<subSubSection pageNumber="361" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="361">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="361">Note:</emphasis>
Although 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="361">Lejeunia</emphasis>
, n.s., 75: 110. 1975) stated &quot;Type: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="…LINN”">...LINN&quot;</normalizedToken>
, this is not accepted as a formal typification, for the reasons explained by Cafferty &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="361">Taxon</emphasis>
49: 240. 2000). Meikle (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="361">Fl. Cyprus</emphasis>
2: 1808. 23 Apr 1985) indicated unspecified material in LINN as type but did not distinguish between sheets 93.32 and 93.33 (which are not part of a single gathering so Art. 9.15 does not apply). 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
typification from later in 1985 therefore stands.
</paragraph>
